# Styling Rules

- Use Tailwind utility classes only
- Use the default Tailwind colour palette
- Keep the UI simple, clean, and functional
- Use mobile-first responsive design only where necessary
- Do not create component-specific CSS files
- Use globals.css only for CSS variables and base styles
- Do not use custom CSS
- Do not add animations, complex layouts, background images, or decorative styling

## Visual Constraints

- Use simple layouts (flex, grid where necessary)
- Use rounded corners and basic shadows via Tailwind utilities only
- Use standard spacing and sizing utilities
- Use clear contrast for readability
- Avoid unnecessary styling decisions
- If a styling choice increases complexity, choose the simpler option